  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBasicBlock

    public class Block
extends Object
implements IBasicBlock
    Block implements IBasicBlock and is the normal representation of a vertex in a method's flowgraph.

      • canFallThrough

        public boolean canFallThrough()
        Determines if control can fall through the end of the Block. This will look back through the Block's instructions, skipping any non-exectuable instructions such as debug instructions. Returns, throws, and unconditional branches will not fall through, but conditional branches and all other instructions will fall through.
        Specified by:
        canFallThrough in interface IBasicBlock
        Returns:
        true if control can fall through this Block.
